The  Atlanta Hawks  beat the visiting
Indiana Pacers 102-91 to level their National Basketball
Association playoff series at two games apiece.  The best-of-seven first-round series now returns to
Indianapolis for Game 5 on May 1.  Also in the Eastern Conference tonight, the Brooklyn Nets
avoided elimination with a 110-91 home win against the Bulls,
who lead the series by three games to two ahead of Game 6 in
 Chicago  on May 2.  The Oklahoma City Thunder, the top seed in the Western
Conference, would sweep the Rockets with a win in Houston in
